~ using potion ~
 
 Running a script or code.
 
   $ bin/potion example/fib.pn
   $ bin/potion -e "code"
 
 Dump the AST and bytecode inspection for a script. 
 
   $ bin/potion -V example/fib.pn
 
 Compiling to bytecode.
 
   $ bin/potion -c example/fib.pn
   $ bin/potion example/fib.pnb
 
 Potion builds its JIT compiler by default, but
 you can use the bytecode VM by running scripts
 with the -B flag.
 If you built with JIT=0, then the bytecode VM
 will run by default.
 
 **It works
 bin/./potion
export PATH=$PATH:/home/tomgdow/potion/bin/


